Nollywood actor, Wale Akorede, popularly known as Okunnu, has called out Nigerian leaders over the state of the nation. Okunnu, in an Instagram post, laid generational curses on Nigerian leaders who have contributed to the worsening state of the nation. In a video shared on his Instagram page, Okunnu wondered when Nigerians will start enjoying a good life. The actor said: ”Nigeria is bad. Whether a man, woman, child, an elderly person who has a hand in making the nation what it is today, their lives will also be bad from generation to generation. “All those who contributed to making Nigeria as bad as it is today, their lives will also be bad from generation to generation. “I have never be in this mood in my life, where we are going in this county. When are we going to enjoy ourselves in this country.” VIDEO:   A post shared by Wale Akorede Okunnu (@okunnu_1) 